The paper deals with modeling intercell interference in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper deals with deriving analytical expressions for network performance metrics such as outage probability and ergodic capacity. The second most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with modeling interference in a multiuser cellular network. The third most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with modeling and analyzing the behavior of a complex system (a wireless network). The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the paper deals with evaluating network performance metrics that are relevant to multimedia applications (such as capacity and fairness). The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.PF (Performance), as the paper deals with evaluating the performance of a wireless network under different conditions.
